# Styling & Design Standards

## Tailwind CSS Rules
- Use Tailwind CSS classes only - no custom CSS unless absolutely necessary
- Follow mobile-first responsive design (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`)
- Use consistent spacing scale (4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, etc.)
- Leverage shadcn-ui components when possible

## Color System
- Primary accent color: Slytherin-green (#22c55e)
- Use semantic color tokens: `text-foreground`, `bg-background`, `border-border`
- Maintain 4.5:1 color contrast ratio for accessibility
- Support both dark and light modes

## Typography
- Use consistent text sizing: `text-sm`, `text-base`, `text-lg`, `text-xl`, etc.
- Apply proper heading hierarchy: `text-4xl md:text-5xl` for main headings
- Use `font-semibold` and `font-bold` for emphasis
- Apply `text-muted-foreground` for secondary text

## Responsive Design
- Test on mobile (375px), tablet (768px), and desktop (1024px+)
- Use responsive utilities: `flex flex-col md:flex-row`
- Ensure touch targets are minimum 44x44px
- Use `container mx-auto` for content width

## Component Patterns
- Use `portfolio-card` class for consistent card styling
- Apply hover states: `hover:bg-primary/90 transition-colors`
- Use `btn-primary` for primary buttons
- Implement loading states with opacity and cursor changes

## Accessibility
- Include proper ARIA labels and roles
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide focus indicators

## Animation Guidelines
- Use `fade-in` class for entrance animations
- Apply `transition-colors` for smooth state changes
- Keep animations subtle and purposeful
- Use `scroll-smooth` for navigation
